Since this is a frontend-only project for now, your `.gitignore` can stay lightweight. It ensures that system clutter or sensitive configuration settings don't accidentally get pushed to your clean canvas.

```text
# Operating System Files
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini

# IDEs and Text Editors
.vscode/
.idea/
*.suo
*.ntvs*
*.njsproj
*.sln
*.swp

# Local Server / Environment logs
*.log
.env
.env.local